# Slot-Based Combat Architecture

Eliminate the "Lemming Train" and "Blob" problems by replacing the current atomic collision-bumping system with a structured **Slot Ring** architecture. Every unit has a finite number of melee engagement slots around it. Attackers must claim a slot before advancing; if no slot is available, they enter a `SCREENING` state‚ÄĒhalting behind the frontline and waiting to replace fallen comrades.

This applies **universally** to all units on both teams.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Data Layer ‚ÄĒ Unit Config & SlotManager

#### [MODIFY] [units.js](file:///e:/WebGames/Onigiri/src/config/units.js)

Add `maxMeleeSlots` to every unit definition. Values are derived from the unit's `radius`:

| Unit | maxMeleeSlots | Reasoning |
|---|---|---|
| Bamboo Barricade | 6 | Wide structure, multiple attack faces |
| Yumi Archer | 2 | Ranged‚ÄĒrarely melee'd, small profile |
| Horoku Siege | 2 | Rarely engaged in melee |
| Hatamoto | 3 | Medium shield unit |
| Takeda Cavalry | 2 | Fast, transient contact |
| Samurai Champion | 5 | Large hero unit |
| Ikki Rebel | 3 | Small enemy, basic fighter |
| Tengu Flier | 2 | Agile flying unit |
| Onmyoji | 2 | Support, stays back |
| Shinobi | 2 | Fast assassin |
| Great Oni (Boss) | 8 | Massive boss, centerpiece of combat |

**Bypass Rules ‚ÄĒ who skips slot-claiming as an attacker:**

| Unit Type | Slot-claiming? | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `ranged` (Yumi Archer) | ‚ĚĆ Skip | Stays at range, never enters melee |
| `siege` (Horoku Siege) | ‚ĚĆ Skip | Lobs projectiles, never advances to melee |
| `support` (Onmyoji) | ‚ĚĆ Skip | Healer, never attacks |
| `cavalry` (while charging) | ‚ĚĆ Skip | Charge is a collision move, not sustained melee |
| `melee`, `hero`, `boss`, `assassin`, `flying` | ‚úÖ Must claim | All engage in direct contact melee |

> [!NOTE]
> Ranged/siege units still **own** a `meleeSlots` array ‚ÄĒ because melee enemies can target them and need to queue around them cleanly. The bypass only applies when they are the *attacker*, not the *target*.

#### [NEW] [SlotManager.js](file:///e:/WebGames/Onigiri/src/systems/SlotManager.js)

A new utility module responsible for managing melee slot state on units. Every unit gets a `meleeSlots` runtime array (initialized at spawn). The `SlotManager` provides three pure functions used by `CombatSystem`:

```js
// Returns the {x, y} coordinate of a free slot on `target`, or null if all slots are full.
claimSlot(attacker, target)  ‚Üí { slotIdx, slotX, slotY } | null

// Called when an attacker dies, changes target, or disengages.
releaseSlot(attacker, target)

// Recalculates all slot coordinates if a target moves (called each frame for moving targets).
updateSlotPositions(target)
```

**Slot geometry:** Slots are arranged evenly in a semicircle facing the attacker's approach direction.
- Enemies attack from above ‚Üí slots are on the top half of the target's radius.
- Players attack from below ‚Üí slots are on the bottom half of the target's radius.
- The slot coordinate is: `target.x + cos(angle) * (target.radius + attacker.radius + 5)`, `target.y + sin(angle) * (target.radius + attacker.radius + 5)`.

