## Verification Plan

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There are no automated tests in this project. All verification is manual in-browser.

### How to Run

```bash
# From the project root:
npm run dev
# Open http://localhost:5173 in a browser
```

### Manual Test Scenarios

| # | Scenario | Steps | Expected Result |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Basic Blob Test** | Start Level 1. Let 15+ Rebels charge a single Hatamoto guard. | ‚Č§3 Rebels actively strike the Hatamoto. The rest halt cleanly in a line behind them. No jitter blob. |
| 2 | **Slot Refill (Replace fallen)** | Same as above. Let the Hatamoto die. | The first Rebel from the screening line instantly steps forward to claim a slot on the next target. No hesitation/jitter. |
| 3 | **Player Attack Slots** | Send 10 Samurai Hatamotos to attack a single Great Oni boss. | ‚Č§8 Hatamotos engage the Oni in a ring. Remaining Hatamotos halt in `SCREENING` behind them. |
| 4 | **Slot Release on Target Death** | Let player units kill an enemy. | The `meleeSlots` array on the dead unit is irrelevant (unit is removed). All attackers that had slots on it should immediately re-target and re-claim slots. No units should freeze permanently. |
| 5 | **No Regression: Ranged Units** | Deploy Yumi Archers. | Archers should be unaffected ‚ÄĒ they never enter melee, so `SCREENING` is never triggered for them. They fire normally. |
| 6 | **Performance Check** | Start a max-unit battle (full barracks vs. large wave). | Frame rate should be **equal or better** than before (fewer separation physics resolves per frame). |

